    "ts": "2026-05-07T21:05:00+00:00",
    "headline": "How a Deal Announcement Overshadowed Akamai Earnings—and Sent the Stock Soaring",
    "summary": "Akamai Technologies  stock surged in after-hours trading Thursday after the cloud computing company announced a “leading frontier model provider” has committed $1.8 billion for its cloud infrastructure services, a sign that the artificial intelligence wave continues to bolster its business.  The announcement came as Akamai posted first-quarter earnings of $1.61 a share, compared with $1.70 a share a year ago and just above Wall Street’s $1.60 a share expectation.  Revenue was led by a 40% increase in cloud infrastructure services (CIS) revenue while its security segment saw sales increase 11%.",
